com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport

Class Card

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.Card
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IIdentifiable

    public final class Card
extends Object
implements IIdentifiable
    A record of information about an Item that has come from a single source at a given time.

    For example, records of information about an individual might come from multiple sources. Each record is stored in a separate Card corresponding to the source. If Items are merged, their Card collections are combined.

    Alternatively, some information about an individual can vary over time: hair color, height, weight, and so on. Separate Cards can retain all of this information, rather than losing it after an update.

    The following table shows two Cards with information about the same individual. All data from both sources is shown, along with the dates associated with that data.

    Property Card 1 Card 2
    Name GARCIA, Jose Luis Lu Garcia
    FBI Number 0345123
    Date of Birth 02 Sep 1960
    Sex M
    Race Hispanic
    Age 50 44
    Hair Color Gray Brown
    Height 600
    Weight 175
    Hair Length Shoulder length Shorter than collar length
    (Source Date) 14 Apr 2010 15 Dec 2004
    (Source Reference) FBI_603A4 DOC1181

    The information in a Card might come from a source item, a merge operation, an external data source, or from manual data entry. A Card might not contain values for all possible Propertys or PropertyGroups on an Item; it could be a partial set of data.

    1.0
